==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inwrought
<hw>In*wrought"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>p. p. ⟦or⟧ a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>in-</ets> + <ets>wrought</ets>. Cf. <er>Inwork</er>.]</ety>
<def>Wrought or worked in or among other things; worked into any fabric
so as to from a part of its texture; wrought or adorned, as with
figures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His mantle hairy, and his bonnet sedge,⟦br⟧
<qex>Inwrought</qex> with figures dim.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Io</ent>⟦br⟧
